-- Canada's Harper Shuffles Cabinet With Baird Replacing Hill as House Leader
-- Theophilos Argitis
-- 2010-08-06T14:12:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/canada-s-harper-shuffles-cabinet-with-baird-replacing-hill-as-house-leader.html

          
          
             Canadian Prime Minister Stephen
Harper made changes to his cabinet that included replacing his
partyâ€™s leader in the legislature.  
 Jay Hill, Conservative House Leader, will be replaced by
Transport Minister John Baird. Indian Affairs Minister Chuck
Strahl will replace Baird at the transport department.
Conservative lawmaker John Duncan will replace Strahl at the
Indian affairs department.  
 Harper made the changes after Hill announced he would not
seek re-election.  
